    "Id": "chassisdef_cadenza_CD77-ZA",
    "Name": "Cadenza",
    "Details": "The CD77-ZA is an 80-ton joint Capellan-Canopian fire support platform built around exceptional survivability. Reinforced Structure combined with 13.5 tons of Ferro-Fibrous armor makes it extraordinarily difficult to put down. An Artemis IV-guided Enhanced LRM 15, a Rotary AC/2, and twin Light PPCs deliver sustained ranged pressure while three jump jets provide unexpected repositioning options for a machine this heavy.\n\n<b><color=#e62e00>Quirk: Reinforced Structure</color></b>\n\n<b><color=#e62e00>Drop Cost Multiplier: 1.12</color></b>",
    "Icon": "NEEDS_ICON"
